sentences: Saunders was born on September 23, 1954 in Montgomery, Alabama to John Baker Saunders, Sr. and Charleen I. Greer.
In 1994, Saunders went into a Minneapolis drug rehabilitation facility, where he met Pearl Jam's Mike McCready.
Mad Season's 1995 album Above was awarded a gold record for sales in the United States.
In 1997, when Mad Season vocalist Layne Staley left the band, the remaining members tried to revive the band by finding a new singer.
Saunders had a relapse with heroin and died from an overdose on January 15, 1999.
In 2002, Mad Season vocalist Layne Staley also died of an overdose, leaving Barrett Martin, and Mike McCready as the only members of Mad Season still alive.

sentences: John Baker Saunders, Jr. (September 23, 1954 – January 15, 1999) was an American musician, known as a founding member and bassist for the American grunge rock supergroup Mad Season, as well as a member of The Walkabouts.
He attended North Shore Country Day School, Rye Country Day School, Fay School, New Trier High School (East), Cabrillo College and Providence College.
